  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Tennessee offers a variety of stunning and unique venues that are perfect for hosting a prom. Here are some great options across the state:\n\n### **Nashville Area**\n1. **The Parthenon** (Nashville)  \n   - A full-scale replica of the original Parthenon in Athens, this iconic venue offers a grand and elegant setting for a prom.\n\n2. **Musicians Hall of Fame and Museum** (Nashville)  \n   - A music-themed venue with a modern vibe, perfect for a fun and memorable prom night.\n\n3. **Schermerhorn Symphony Center** (Nashville)  \n   - A beautiful and sophisticated venue with an elegant ballroom and acoustically perfect spaces.\n\n4. **Gaylord Opryland Resort** (Nashville)  \n   - This sprawling resort offers multiple event spaces, including atriums with lush gardens and waterfalls.\n\n### **Knoxville Area**\n5. **The Historic Southern Railway Station** (Knoxville)  \n   - A historic train station with a blend of vintage charm and modern amenities.\n\n6. **The Press Room** (Knoxville)  \n   - A trendy and industrial-chic venue located in a historic building downtown.\n\n7. **The Tennessean Hotel** (Knoxville)  \n   - A luxurious hotel with elegant event spaces and stunning views.\n\n### **Memphis Area**\n8. **The Peabody Memphis** (Memphis)  \n   - A historic hotel with classic Southern charm and a beautiful grand ballroom.\n\n9. **The Memphian** (Memphis)  \n   - A modern and stylish hotel with versatile event spaces in the heart of the city.\n\n10. **The Cannon Center for the Performing Arts** (Memphis)  \n   - A grand venue with a theater and ballroom, ideal for a large-scale prom.\n\n### **Chattanooga Area**\n11. **The Chattanooga Choo Choo** (Chattanooga)  \n   - A historic train station turned hotel with unique event spaces, including gardens and vintage train cars.\n\n12. **The Read House** (Chattanooga)  \n   - A historic hotel with elegant ballrooms and a touch of Southern charm.\n\n13. **The Tennessee Aquarium** (Chattanooga)  \n   - A truly unique venue where guests can celebrate surrounded by aquatic exhibits.\n\n### **Middle Tennessee and Beyond**\n14. **Loveless Cafe Barn** (Nashville area)  \n   - A rustic and charming barn venue with a cozy, country feel.\n\n15. **The Factory at Franklin** (Franklin)  \n   - A historic industrial space turned event venue with a trendy and versatile atmosphere.\n\n16. **Montgomery Bell State Park** (Burns)  \n   - A scenic park with event facilities surrounded by nature, perfect for a more relaxed prom.\n\n### **East Tennessee**\n17. **The Standard at the Smith House** (Knoxville)  \n   - A restored historic home with elegant event spaces and a Southern charm.\n\n18. **The Mill & Mine** (Knoxville)  \n   - A modern, industrial-style venue with a large capacity and flexible layout.\n\n### **General Tips**\n- Always check the venue\u2019s capacity, available dates, and any restrictions (e.g., catering or decor).\n- Consider nearby accommodations for students who may need to stay overnight.\n- Look into venues that offer customizable lighting, sound, and staging options.\n\nTennessee\u2019s diverse locations provide something for every prom theme, whether you\u2019re looking for elegance, historic charm, or a unique atmosphere.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
